From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Aneesh Pradhan <aneeshpradhan@acm.org>
Date: Wed, 22 Jul 2026 20:45:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 8/8] arm64: dts: qcom: perry: enable PMI8950 flash LEDs

Perry routes front and rear camera flash/torch through the PMI8950 flash
LED peripheral at 0xd300 (downstream qcom,qpnp-flash-led with flash0/1 +
torch0/1). Mainline already has:

  - pmi8950.dtsi: pmi8950_flash led-controller@d300 (disabled) with
    compatible "qcom,spmi-flash-led-v1"
  - drivers/leds/flash/leds-qcom-flash-v1.c (CONFIG_LEDS_QCOM_FLASH_V1)

Enable both channels the same way as other msm89x7 Motorola boards
(montana, hannah, cedric). Currents match the stock board (torch <=200 mA,
flash <=1000 mA, timeout 1.28 s).

Signed-off-by: Aneesh Pradhan <aneeshpradhan@acm.org>
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/msm8917-motorola-perry-common.dtsi | 25 +++++++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 25 insertions(+)

--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/msm8917-motorola-perry-common.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/msm8917-motorola-perry-common.dtsi
@@ -259,6 +259,36 @@
 	status = "okay";
 };
 
+
+/*
+ * Camera flash/torch (PMI8950 channels). Driver: leds-qcom-flash-v1.
+ * Channel map (torch-tested): led@0 = rear, led@1 = front.
+ * Currents match stock: torch <=200 mA, flash <=1000 mA.
+ */
+&pmi8950_flash {
+	#address-cells = <1>;
+	#size-cells = <0>;
+	status = "okay";
+
+	led@0 {
+		reg = <0>;
+		function = LED_FUNCTION_FLASH;
+		color = <LED_COLOR_ID_WHITE>;
+		led-max-microamp = <200000>;
+		flash-max-microamp = <1000000>;
+		flash-max-timeout-us = <1280000>;
+	};
+
+	led@1 {
+		reg = <1>;
+		function = LED_FUNCTION_FLASH;
+		color = <LED_COLOR_ID_WHITE>;
+		led-max-microamp = <200000>;
+		flash-max-microamp = <1000000>;
+		flash-max-timeout-us = <1280000>;
+	};
+};
+
 &gps_mem {
 	status = "okay";
 };
